  "text": "The geometry around the neck for a static black hole in the Boulware vacuum was discussed above in Sec.2.1. In this section, we study the dynamical geometry around the neck for a black hole with the back-reaction from the vacuum energy-momentum tensor for the Unruh vacuum. The geometry is obtained by introducing the Hawking radiation as perturbation to the static case of Sec. 2.1. As a simple model for the collapsing matter, we consider a thin shell falling at the speed of light. The matter distribution in the radial direction is approximated by the Dirac delta function. [CITATION_1] We will study the dynamical geometry outside the collapsing matter [CITATION_2] . The geometry for a collapsing thin shell can be obtained by connecting this exterior geometry with the interior geometry (which is flat spacetime) at the collapsing shell. We will first consider the generic amplitude β(u) of Hawking radiation, and then determine the Hawking radiation by imposing the junction condition on the collapsing shell.",
